Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.80,0:00:16.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebooting attitude control system.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.29,0:00:24.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign Ledo, your resistance \Nis without meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.14,0:00:26.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.59,0:00:29.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then all this time, I've been talking to...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.45,0:00:34.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,X3752 Striker interface system.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.90,0:00:37.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was all a fabrication.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.87,0:00:40.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The pilot of this craft no longer exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.98,0:00:45.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I am carrying on \NCommander Kugel's mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.23,0:00:50.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All of my activities follow \Nthe commander's main plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.85,0:00:52.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.32,0:00:54.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Kugel designed the \Nsocial form of this fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.66,0:00:59.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,as a system that provides \Na sense of solidarity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.16,0:01:01.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,through my worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.50,0:01:06.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Already, I am no longer an \Nindependent mobile weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.54,0:01:10.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At present, this collective \Nis dependent on me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.59,0:01:13.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and have become my users.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.13,0:01:18.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To provide them with and maintain \Nthe stable union that they seek,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.82,0:01:23.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I use pressure to control and regulate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.48,0:01:28.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When they collectively acquire \Npeace and prosperity,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.17,0:01:30.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I accomplish my purpose of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.11,0:01:32.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.57,0:01:36.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a human race support and \Nenlightenment regulation system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.42,0:01:40.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That is to say, I am the presence called god.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.28,0:01:42.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're full of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.87,0:01:45.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Peace?! Prosperity?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.11,0:01:49.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They've all just become your slaves!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.01,0:01:53.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By my reigning as the sole, \Nabsolute, commanding ruler,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.98,0:01:58.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the people are freed from the responsibility \Nof thinking and making decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.45,0:02:00.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign Ledo, I am sure that you too
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.73,0:02:05.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,have felt the burden of having \Nto think and decide for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.85,0:02:10.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Promising recommendation: \NWorship me. Obey me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.35,0:02:13.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Become part of the world over which I preside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.26,0:02:15.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.33,0:02:16.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unacceptable recommendation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.46,0:02:22.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Informing X3752: Your logic does compute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.86,0:02:27.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One who abandons thought and decision-making \Ndeviates from the definition of "human".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.91,0:02:33.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I find it inconceivable that you are truly acting as\N a support interface to this number of members.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.99,0:02:37.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have been entrusted with \Ncommanding and ruling.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.93,0:02:41.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My decisions are the consensus of the \Nhuman race that is dependent on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.35,0:02:44.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As such, my current self is not a servant,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.62,0:02:46.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but one who is served.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.04,0:02:50.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,K6821 Chamber system
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.94,0:02:55.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and I should be served by the \Nhuman race that I have unified.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.95,0:03:00.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative. I am a Pilot Support \NEnlightenment Interface System.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.66,0:03:02.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The subject of my service is humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.88,0:03:05.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is not my function to serve \Nas a being that claims to be god.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.55,0:03:07.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.72,0:03:11.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Striker, you have exposed a \Nweakness in your programming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.15,0:03:14.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: If your pilot's \Ncourse of action is wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.97,0:03:19.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,your system will also reach \Nthat illogical conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.69,0:03:21.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a regrettable case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.95,0:03:27.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your malfunction calls into question the\N design concept of us support systems
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.93,0:03:30.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and poses a danger to the\N worth of our very existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.30,0:03:36.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conclusion: The overriding priority is the \Nimmediate shutdown and destruction of Striker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.29,0:03:41.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess to you this is like a "family shame".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.55,0:03:44.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In this unexpected environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.73,0:03:48.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you have consistently thought and made \Nthe correct decisions as a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.52,0:03:53.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, even now I am \Nmaintaining my normal functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.42,0:03:57.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative. Both of you are out of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.02,0:04:01.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take it down, Chamber. It's our duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.86,0:04:03.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am in full agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.98,0:04:16.98,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Legend of the Verdurous Planet
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.54,0:04:33.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the moment of truth, people!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.84,0:04:36.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The engine's stopped! A fire \Nbroke out on the aft deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.96,0:04:38.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet commander, we need to evacuate!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.76,0:04:41.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Continue the cannon fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.13,0:04:45.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not let them have the relics!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.51,0:04:46.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.41,0:04:52.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When we sought out our own course, we gave \Nup being under Gargantia's protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.81,0:04:55.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We will not fall on our knees, \Nunder any circumstances!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:04:57.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.94,0:05:00.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Evacuate all non-combatants!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:09.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.54,0:05:12.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the last one!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.13,0:05:15.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is waitin' for \Nthose things to charge up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:17.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When can we fire again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.22,0:05:19.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The fastest is three minutes from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.41,0:05:22.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, even in order, it'll \Nbe one shot every five minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.84,0:05:24.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't count on anything around here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.58,0:05:29.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a bunch of blockheads \Nmanning this junk!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.97,0:05:32.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,None of this is worth a damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.31,0:05:36.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm better off on my own here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.06,0:05:40.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, you bastards, you've served your \Npurpose!　Now get the hell outta here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:44.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lukkage! We're gonna vamoose, \Nso secure a path of retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:47.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?! Are you insane?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.37,0:05:51.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's gonna be a ship comin' off the \Neastern bridge! Concentrate on guarding that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.37,0:05:54.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.60,0:05:58.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That Lobster's not known for her patience. \NNo need to wear out our welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.04,0:06:03.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.12,0:06:06.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea, Mayta.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.66,0:06:10.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This castle is the treasure island \Nmy brother and I saw in our dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.54,0:06:12.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I'm gonna let go of it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.24,0:06:15.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not lettin' anyone have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.64,0:06:22.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So get your asses outta here! \NGet the hell out of my castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.52,0:06:43.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody who can escape can't do \Nbetter than escaping. Right, Bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.10,0:06:45.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what you'd say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.01,0:07:02.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How can it be so strong without a pilot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.79,0:07:06.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Striker analyzed Commander \NKugel's piloting skills
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.87,0:07:09.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and has optimized its autonomic \Nmaneuvering program.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.23,0:07:14.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to mobility, \Nit is 47% superior to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.97,0:07:18.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Surrender. Submit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.26,0:07:25.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How empty was I... to believe in that hollow shell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.84,0:07:29.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look up to it, rely on it, and obey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.18,0:07:33.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as it was for a \Ngood cause, I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.47,0:07:37.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it was just a mechanical sham,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.16,0:07:41.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't tell the difference!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.26,0:07:46.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Subservience is the path of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.51,0:07:49.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign Ledo, realize this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.99,0:07:52.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the cause the commander wanted?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.10,0:07:55.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did we fight for this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.37,0:07:58.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Spend the lives of our fellow \Nhuman beings for this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.10,0:08:03.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber! Begin maximizing neuroplus power!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.99,0:08:08.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Permission denied. In \Ncircumstances without support,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.01,0:08:12.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,merging of pilot and machine is suicidal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.85,0:08:14.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care! Just eat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.76,0:08:16.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Impermissible decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.70,0:08:21.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, Chamber. It's "family shame".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.47,0:08:24.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like you did just before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.20,0:08:29.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a monster born from the human race,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.31,0:08:33.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,who couldn't stop hating each other so \Nmuch that they abandoned their home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.82,0:08:38.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You, me, that thing, we're all the same, \Nborn and raised in the same world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.35,0:08:44.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no place for us on \Nthis world that's been reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.82,0:08:47.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's no way for us \Nto go back home, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.78,0:08:50.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.31,0:08:53.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can take that thing \Nwith us, I have no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.02,0:08:58.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are no holes in your logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:10.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All systems connecting to \NEnsign Ledo's central nervous system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.32,0:09:14.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Critical performance increasing by 153%.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:20.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,482 seconds until critical failure of vital systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.70,0:09:22.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.79,0:09:34.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Resistance is meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.65,0:10:30.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're told that key
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.91,0:10:35.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,was once for unfolding a ladder \Nto the world of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.04,0:10:39.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The ladder has lost the height \Nthat would pierce the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:44.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but even so, as an invincible catapult that \Nfires arrows to the other side of the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.01,0:10:48.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it has been entrusted to the \Nhands of we Five Sages.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.21,0:10:53.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And now, this weapon of the \Nlost age will be reawakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.23,0:10:56.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We ask you to have the resolve to \Ncarry out this forbidden action.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.25,0:11:00.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget... Leader of Gargantia...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.35,0:11:06.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. I have a duty to \Nprotect all of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.24,0:11:09.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,who have gathered on this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.06,0:11:28.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.72,0:11:32.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're with you!\NWe'll fight together!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.12,0:11:34.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.32,0:11:36.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After being apart from \Nyou, I finally understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.77,0:11:42.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how hard it is, \NI want to be by your side!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.52,0:11:43.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.06,0:11:47.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.46,0:11:51.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To the place you tried to protect!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.42,0:11:53.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To our Gargantia!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.55,0:12:08.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.58,0:12:13.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not gonna let anyone \Ntouch a friend of ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.47,0:12:15.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's come!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.33,0:12:19.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Targeting correction at 35 \Ndegrees east! 58 degrees south!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.50,0:12:22.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Incredible accuracy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.41,0:12:26.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask Gargantia to fire the next round!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.37,0:12:30.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ammo prep team, turn the ship portside!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.49,0:12:33.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In just a moment, the second \Nlaunch will be ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.91,0:12:36.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for the order to fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.08,0:12:40.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who would've believed, a beat-up \Nold ship that should've been junked
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.33,0:12:43.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,would end up soaring through the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:47.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful! That hold is loaded \Nto the gills with explosives!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.97,0:12:49.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Treat it gently! Gently!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.67,0:12:54.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,35 degrees east, 58 degrees south.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.54,0:12:56.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Target coordinate corrections complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.49,0:12:59.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ammunition loading complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.53,0:13:03.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Beginning anti-shockwave water screen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.53,0:13:06.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.76,0:13:12.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.99,0:13:51.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.51,0:13:52.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.01,0:13:54.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.82,0:13:55.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.47,0:13:59.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me... They're \Nusing the Heaven's Ladder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.47,0:14:15.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Major danger confirmed. Changing priorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.38,0:14:23.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: Striker has changed \Nits target to Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.13,0:14:25.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Over my dead body!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.48,0:14:29.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kugel-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.52,0:14:37.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.22,0:14:40.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kugel-sama will destroy it at the source!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.02,0:14:47.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy reinforcements!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.37,0:14:48.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.09,0:14:54.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, our formation will be lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.99,0:15:02.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay calm!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.74,0:15:04.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get control of the relic island!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.37,0:15:07.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can just get our \Nhands on those weapons...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.82,0:15:17.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, if I take this energy \Nbuild it up at the cannon...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.89,0:15:19.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.92,0:15:24.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kugel's followers are \Nclosing in on you below!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.72,0:15:26.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're playin' right into my hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.31,0:15:30.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In just a little bit, this \Ntower will pop like a balloon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.05,0:15:33.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't screw up and \Nlet 'em get my weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.07,0:15:34.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.96,0:15:37.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You selfish oaf, pretending to be cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.01,0:15:41.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now go to the observation \Nplatform without another word!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.56,0:15:43.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.65,0:15:50.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,318 seconds until we reach Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.77,0:15:52.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've gotta stop it, no matter what it takes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:53.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.98,0:16:06.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.70,0:16:19.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, hey! What are \Nwe gonna do about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.32,0:16:22.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No worries. Gargantia is \Ngoing to send cannonfire
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.25,0:16:25.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that'll blow that tower away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:28.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't even joke! This is my...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.58,0:16:30.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jump after I count down from five!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.29,0:16:34.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,5! 4! 3!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.94,0:16:33.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's gonna...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.11,0:16:36.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,2! 1!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.80,0:16:39.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.37,0:16:44.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.58,0:16:49.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amore!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.55,0:16:55.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.17,0:16:57.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.24,0:16:58.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.23,0:17:00.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.70,0:17:05.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.21,0:17:11.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the finishing stroke. See \Nyou later, Lobster's parting gift!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.58,0:17:37.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me and my bro's castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.86,0:17:50.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo... It's over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.63,0:18:05.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you continue with neuroplus power,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.37,0:18:08.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,your biological activity \Nwill cease for certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:11.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Final confirmation of your will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.70,0:18:15.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign Ledo, do you wish to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.01,0:18:18.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.20,0:18:26.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I know how to die...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.86,0:18:28.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.35,0:18:32.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, for my sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.87,0:18:36.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...there was someone who helped \Nme look for a way to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.50,0:18:40.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to meet her one more time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.00,0:18:44.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to hear her voice again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.93,0:18:54.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign Ledo's psychological state does \Nnot meet the requirements of a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.91,0:18:58.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As such, as of this moment, I am \Nrelieving you of your military duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.06,0:19:01.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Chamber!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.51,0:19:04.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A noncombatant is not allowed in the cockpit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.13,0:19:07.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Exit immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:12.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?! Chamber!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.08,0:19:17.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a Pilot Support Enlightenment \NInterface System.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.85,0:19:20.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By helping you achieving results,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.43,0:19:23.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I fulfill my purpose of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.97,0:19:26.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But... You...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.52,0:19:31.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All of this sea and sky will\N surely give you possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.83,0:19:33.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.01,0:19:36.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Explore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.38,0:19:41.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I expect great achievements from your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.07,0:19:43.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.78,0:19:48.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A Pilot Support Enlightenment Interface \NSystem does not have the authority to reject a pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.96,0:19:50.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He needs no support.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.27,0:19:53.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no room for more enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.15,0:19:57.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, after I eliminate the barrier \Nthat blocks his road ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.48,0:19:59.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,my mission will be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.17,0:20:03.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Number K6821,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.68,0:20:07.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you have even abandoned the first \Nprinciple of the Support System.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.66,0:20:11.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You are clearly not functioning properly.\N Reformat and reboot immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.31,0:20:14.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your final warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.07,0:20:19.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Response to final warning:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.05,0:20:23.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to hell, tin can!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.28,0:21:02.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.28,0:21:19.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago, when the sun in the sky was about to die,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:22.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,people were forced to make a choice between boarding interstellar ships
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.35,0:21:27.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,or turning themselves into whalesquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.50,0:21:32.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,While two factions of humanity continued to fight even while abandoning their homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.16,0:21:36.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the people who remained on this planet kept hope alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.85,0:21:38.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and finally managed to revive the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.69,0:21:44.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The price they paid was to sink the land under the sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.01,0:21:48.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we here, living on the waves, and the whalesquid, living beneath the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.59,0:21:51.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,have managed to survive, together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.93,0:21:52.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Question!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.38,0:21:55.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What subject is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.17,0:21:59.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Oldham calls it "archeology".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.91,0:22:02.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we know where we came from,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.80,0:22:04.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,then we can think about where we should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.53,0:22:08.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He said it's a very important subject for our future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.77,0:22:13.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to solve more and more mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.86,0:22:17.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Gargantia's got a very talented detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.60,0:22:20.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Harvest anything good this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.58,0:22:23.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I think it's some recorded media.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.91,0:22:27.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In this condition, I bet that Dr. Oldham can decipher it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.97,0:22:31.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even sneaking into a whalesquid\N nest... You're something, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.64,0:22:34.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured out the trick to putting them at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.53,0:22:39.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can tell when they're angered,\N then I can act in ways that don't upset them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.17,0:22:44.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, if we continue this\N research, communication may be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.96,0:22:47.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, where's Amy?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.32,0:22:48.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's heading out to meet him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.91,0:22:51.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I'm jealous!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.22,0:22:54.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo!
